TALLAHASSEE — Cutting the cost of re-registering vehicles by an average of $25 continued its speedy progress through the Legislature as the Florida Senate unanimously approved the measure Tuesday.

Overall, the cuts will cost the state $309 million in lost revenue next year and nearly $400 million in subsequent years, but it's universally popular in an election year. The measure rolls back fee hikes that the Legislature approved in 2009
